SIMPLE: rejoice
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoice
<hw>Re*joice"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*jois")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rejoiced</conjf>
<pr>(-joist")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Rejoicing</conjf>
<pr>(-joi"s?ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>rejoissen</ets>, OF.
<ets>resjouir</ets>, <ets>resjoir</ets>, F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧jouir</ets>;
pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + OF. <ets>esjouir</ets>, <ets>esjoir</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧jouir</ets>, to rejoice; pref. <ets>es-</ets> (L.
<ets>ex-</ets>) + OF. <ets>jouir</ets>, <ets>joir</ets>, F.
<ets>jouir</ets>, from L. <ets>gaudere</ets> to rejoice. See
<er>Joy</er>.]</ety> <def>To feel joy; to experience gladness in a high
degree; to have pleasurable satisfaction; to be delighted.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧O, <xex>rejoice</xex> beyond a common joy.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will be glad and <qex>rejoice</qex> in thy mercy.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xxxi. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> To delight; joy; exult; triumph.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoice</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoice
<hw>Re*joice"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To enjoy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Peacock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give joy to; to make joyful; to
gladden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I me <qex>rejoysed</qex> of my liberty.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While she, great saint, <qex>rejoices</qex> heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Were he [Cain] alive, it would <qex>rejoice</qex> his soul to see
what mischief it had made.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To please; cheer; exhilarate; delight.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoice</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoice
<hw>Re*joice"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of rejoicing.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoicement</ent>⟦br⟧
